==English==

===Etymology===

* First attested around 1425.
* From {{etyl|frm}} {{term|absorber|lang=frm}}, from {{etyl|fro}} {{term|assorbir|lang=fro}},from {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|absorbeo|absorbeō|swallow up|lang=la}}, from {{term|ab||from|lang=la}} + {{term|sorbeo|sorbeō|suck in, swallow|lang=la}}; akin to {{etyl|grc}} {{term|ῥοφέω|tr=ropheō||sup up|lang=grc}}, {{etyl|mga}} {{term|srub||snout|lang=mga}}, {{etyl|lt}} {{term|srebti|srēbti|to sip|lang=lt}}, and perhaps to {{etyl|gmh}} {{term|surpfeln|sürpfeln|to sip|lang=gmh}}, and {{etyl|no}} {{term|slurpe|lang=no}}.
* Compare French {{term|absorber|lang=fr}}.

